HEADWORD: Zietrisikite
<hw>Zie`tri*si"kite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral wax, vert similar to ozocerite. It is found at
<ets>Zietrisika</ets>, Moldavia, whence its name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

